        "title": "feat(workboard): embed reusable chat surface in card details",
        "body": "## Stack / Dependency Note\n\nThis is Batch F in the OpenClaw-X durable-core stack.\n\nDepends on:\n- PR1 / #97507: durable coordination RFC\n- PR2 / #97508: opt-in durable coordination kernel\n- Batch A / #97666: restart and schema lifecycle proof\n- Batch B / #97667: intake, branch routes, Task Flow projection\n- Batch C / #97668: Workboard durable projection visibility\n- Batch D / #97865: worker execution and recovery hardening\n- Batch E / #97866: ops, storage, and human-signal readiness\n\nGitHub currently shows batch PRs against `main`, so this PR may include earlier dependency commits in the commit list. The intended unique review diff is the Workboard chat UI layer after Batch E.\n\nInternal plan coverage: Workboard chat value proof. The future `chat.send.contextRefs` protocol slice remains PR11b and is not implemented here.\n\n## What Changed\n\n- Makes the main chat surface reusable from non-chat views.\n- Embeds the reusable chat surface into the Workboard card detail drawer.\n- Adds card-scoped Workboard chat actions for new work-unit chat, linked session continuation, and linking the current session.\n- Keeps the current Workboard context as a compatibility text envelope until typed `chat.send.contextRefs` exists.\n- Compacts Workboard controls so the board remains usable when details are open or the viewport is narrow.\n\n## Why\n\nDurable coordination becomes much more visible and useful when operators can discuss a specific Workboard card from the card itself while preserving the card or work-unit context.\n\n## Non-Goals\n\n- No new Gateway protocol field in this batch.\n- No generic `metadata: any` on `chat.send`.\n- No Workboard-owned durable state.\n- No workflow designer UI.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `npm test -- src/durable/worker.test.ts src/durable/recovery.test.ts src/durable/executor.test.ts src/durable/routes.test.ts src/durable/sqlite-store.test.ts src/durable/store-factory.test.ts src/durable/human-signal.test.ts src/durable/taskflow-bridge.test.ts src/durable/intake.test.ts src/durable/fan-in.test.ts ui/src/ui/app-chat.test.ts ui/src/ui/controllers/workboard.test.ts ui/src/ui/views/workboard.test.ts ui/src/ui/app-render.helpers.browser.test.ts`\n- `npm run ui:build`",
        "branch": "codex/openclaw-durable-batch-f-workboard-chat",
